      • getLeapSecondsKnown

        public boolean getLeapSecondsKnown()
        The value TRUE of the attribute LeapSecondsKnown shall indicate that the value for SecondSinceEpoch takes into account all leap seconds occurred. If it is FALSE then the value does not take into account the leap seconds that occurred before the initialization of the time source of the device.
        Returns:
        TRUE of the attribute LeapSecondsKnown shall indicate that the value for SecondSinceEpoch takes into account all leap seconds occurred

      • getClockFailure

        public boolean getClockFailure()
        The attribute clockFailure shall indicate that the time source of the sending device is unreliable. The value of the TimeStamp shall be ignored.
        Returns:
        true if the time source of the sending device is unreliable

      • getClockNotSynchronized

        public boolean getClockNotSynchronized()
        The attribute clockNotSynchronized shall indicate that the time source of the sending device is not synchronized with the external UTC time.
        Returns:
        true if the time source of the sending device is not synchronized

      • getTimeAccuracy

        public int getTimeAccuracy()
        The attribute TimeAccuracy shall represent the time accuracy class of the time source of the sending device relative to the external UTC time. The timeAccuracy classes shall represent the number of significant bits in the FractionOfSecond

        If the time is set via Java Date objects, the accuracy is 1 ms, that is a timeAccuracy value of 10.

        Returns:
        the time accuracy
